@kone12185334 Any patriotic Kol understands one thing: although it is the father who sends dog food, the public is his base.
Endorsing his father, the final outcome is to be sacrificed by his father. Only by having a base can one guarantee his right to speak, so that even if he is still sacrificed in the end, he can still have a reputation of "persisting in telling the truth".
So Lao Hu really devoted himself to his work, and his loyalty is more than an order of magnitude stronger than that of these people.
